trans-unit.source: Contains a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
ASP.NET health monitoring allows production and operations staff to manage deployed Web applications.
The <xref:System.Web.Management> namespace contains the health event types responsible for packaging application health-status data and the provider types responsible for processing this data.
It also contains supporting types that help during the management of health events.
The <xref:System.Web.Management.WebBaseEventCollection> class is used to deliver a collection of health-monitoring events to providers such as the <xref:System.Web.Management.SqlWebEventProvider>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEventCollection"></xref> class.

The <xref:System.Web.Management.WebBaseEventCollection.%23ctor%28System.Collections.ICollection%29> constructor allows you to create an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Management.WebBaseEventCollection> class and initialize it with a collection of <xref:System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent> objects.
The collection of <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent"></xref> objects.
events is `null`.
Indicates whether the collection contains the specified <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.Web.Management.WebBaseEvent"></xref> object to search for.
`true` if the collection contains the specified element; otherwise, `false`.
